00:46:39.240 --> 00:46:41.742
unlike his opening statements where we

00:46:41.802 --> 00:46:44.806
could redirect the mood by changing Dowd's

00:46:44.865 --> 00:46:47.047
expression to the cohortative,

00:46:47.527 --> 00:46:51.010
making this a conveyance of his desire,

00:46:51.610 --> 00:46:52.992
that does not work with,

00:46:53.932 --> 00:46:56.514
I want you to conceal your presence,

00:46:56.574 --> 00:46:58.436
would it?

00:46:58.496 --> 00:46:58.836
That is,

00:46:58.916 --> 00:47:01.139
unless he actually wants God to look away

00:47:01.179 --> 00:47:03.221
and to go away,

00:47:03.420 --> 00:47:04.402
and that would be worse.

00:47:06.364 --> 00:47:08.987
Yahuwah is deeply vested in humanity.

00:47:09.067 --> 00:47:10.668
He wants us to live up to his

00:47:10.748 --> 00:47:13.389
expectations and to demonstrate that we

00:47:13.429 --> 00:47:17.552
can be perceptive, reflective, responsive,

00:47:17.911 --> 00:47:21.653
and reliable in our inclinations and

00:47:21.713 --> 00:47:25.697
disposition, especially in our judgment.

00:47:27.157 --> 00:47:32.760
But this is only an imperative in the

00:47:32.820 --> 00:47:35.342
sense that if we fail, we're done.

00:47:36.710 --> 00:47:40.492
And yet, of course, that is on us,

00:47:41.572 --> 00:47:43.132
not him.

00:47:44.954 --> 00:47:45.974
It is true, however,

00:47:46.014 --> 00:47:48.556
that Yahowah found a way to resolve his

00:47:48.615 --> 00:47:50.376
son's emotional outburst while

00:47:50.496 --> 00:47:53.077
reestablishing, I should say,

00:47:53.657 --> 00:47:55.679
a more appropriate sense of right and

00:47:55.719 --> 00:47:58.201
wrong for the king.

00:47:58.300 --> 00:47:58.880
And for that,

00:47:59.280 --> 00:48:03.083
he would dispatch the most judgmental soul

00:48:03.824 --> 00:48:04.563
in his arsenal.

00:48:06.320 --> 00:48:08.842
Yada, the par bull.

00:48:10.264 --> 00:48:12.224
But even then, the Ba'al,

00:48:12.244 --> 00:48:15.248
a master of pertinent da'ath, knowledge,

00:48:15.949 --> 00:48:19.170
would not be deployed as an uncompromising

00:48:19.331 --> 00:48:22.775
judge of character until the despondent

00:48:22.815 --> 00:48:25.516
son was walked off the ledge by his

00:48:25.597 --> 00:48:27.599
surrogate ‘Amah, mother.

00:48:29.980 --> 00:48:30.619
Now that said,

00:48:30.659 --> 00:48:33.942
Yahowah wasn't about to bara, start over,

00:48:34.302 --> 00:48:37.784
by conceiving something entirely new from

00:48:37.844 --> 00:48:38.463
scratch.

00:48:38.583 --> 00:48:42.326
The existing soul would get his act

00:48:42.346 --> 00:48:45.706
together instead.

00:48:45.746 --> 00:48:47.347
But this is what Dowd had to say,

00:48:47.367 --> 00:48:49.628
and we'll conclude our program with this

00:48:49.688 --> 00:48:51.610
thought.

00:48:51.630 --> 00:48:53.309
You must choose to create.

00:48:54.010 --> 00:48:57.391
It is imperative that you decide to

00:48:57.472 --> 00:48:58.552
fashion and form.

00:48:59.501 --> 00:49:02.523
that which has never previously existed,

00:49:03.844 --> 00:49:06.786
clean and pure, judgment,

00:49:07.106 --> 00:49:08.947
thoughts and emotions,

00:49:09.047 --> 00:49:14.170
inclination and disposition, all for me,

00:49:14.710 --> 00:49:15.092
God.

00:49:16.833 --> 00:49:20.414
Then it is imperative that you decide to

00:49:20.454 --> 00:49:20.934
repair,

00:49:21.375 --> 00:49:24.297
restoring and renewing by appointing a

00:49:24.396 --> 00:49:26.878
firm and establishing a steadfast,

00:49:28.067 --> 00:49:32.329
Ruwach, spirit within me.

00:49:32.371 --> 00:49:35.432
Mizmowr, song, Psalm.

00:49:35.492 --> 00:49:36.052


00:49:37.755 --> 00:49:39.155
I'm going to summarize this and we'll

00:49:39.175 --> 00:49:40.856
return to this passage at the beginning of

00:49:40.916 --> 00:49:41.777
our next program.

00:49:43.518 --> 00:49:43.980
But here,

00:49:44.760 --> 00:49:47.943
Dowd is again projecting on Yahowah.

00:49:49.007 --> 00:49:50.188
and saying that, God,

00:49:50.208 --> 00:49:51.168
you need to start all over.

00:49:51.610 --> 00:49:55.132
Bara means to create something which has

00:49:55.172 --> 00:49:56.311
never existed before.

00:49:56.773 --> 00:49:59.653
You don't bara' to improve that which

00:50:00.014 --> 00:50:00.655
exists.

00:50:01.094 --> 00:50:04.277
You bara' to start from scratch.

00:50:05.097 --> 00:50:07.179
The first word is bara',

00:50:07.798 --> 00:50:10.000
and the opening line of the Towrah,

00:50:10.039 --> 00:50:12.302
and God bara', created.

00:50:13.061 --> 00:50:13.942
Bara' from nothing.

00:50:15.063 --> 00:50:15.443
Bara'

00:50:17.664 --> 00:50:18.465
God is saying,

00:50:18.525 --> 00:50:21.186
you need to start all over again.

00:50:21.248 --> 00:50:24.230
You need to recreate someone with

00:50:25.170 --> 00:50:27.972
judgment, with thoughts and inclinations,

00:50:28.012 --> 00:50:29.132
with disposition.

00:50:29.994 --> 00:50:35.516
So you need to choose to create clean

00:50:35.577 --> 00:50:36.177
and pure,

00:50:36.878 --> 00:50:40.221
to have majestic and brilliant thoughts

00:50:40.260 --> 00:50:40.960
and emotions,

00:50:41.021 --> 00:50:43.282
inclinations and disposition for me.

00:50:44.155 --> 00:50:46.255
It's not my job to get my act

00:50:46.275 --> 00:50:46.615
together.

00:50:46.635 --> 00:50:48.755
It's not my job to become moral and

00:50:48.815 --> 00:50:51.637
righteous and correct.

00:50:51.677 --> 00:50:56.277
It's your job, fix me.

00:50:56.338 --> 00:50:57.117
And oh, by the way,

00:50:57.338 --> 00:50:59.179
that spirit you gave me is broken.

00:51:00.940 --> 00:51:02.860
I need a new Ruwach.

00:51:03.119 --> 00:51:06.621
This one I need to be like more

00:51:06.681 --> 00:51:09.922
reliable, more stable.

00:51:13.871 --> 00:51:17.572
So you need to renew that Ruwach.

00:51:17.592 --> 00:51:24.233
It's hard to imagine him getting the place

00:51:24.253 --> 00:51:25.413
he would say any of these things,

00:51:26.612 --> 00:51:27.152
but he did.

00:51:28.914 --> 00:51:32.813
And that makes the intervention by Leah as

00:51:32.873 --> 00:51:39.695
the ‘Amah and her Ba'al as Yada among

00:51:39.735 --> 00:51:42.396
the most intriguing events

00:51:43.925 --> 00:51:44.985
and all of human history.

00:51:47.086 --> 00:51:47.648
And of course,

00:51:47.708 --> 00:51:50.148
we now know that the final Mashal word

00:51:50.188 --> 00:51:52.771
picture, the thirty-first proverb,

00:51:54.592 --> 00:51:57.695
is what Leah accomplished.

00:51:59.016 --> 00:52:01.197
I have subsequently learned that the

00:52:01.257 --> 00:52:02.918
person who was touting her,

00:52:03.918 --> 00:52:07.201
speaking so brilliantly of her,

00:52:07.521 --> 00:52:08.061
loving her,

00:52:08.802 --> 00:52:11.945
who actually wrote those words that we

00:52:11.985 --> 00:52:12.385
have read,

00:52:13.942 --> 00:52:16.722
It wasn't Dowd.

00:52:16.764 --> 00:52:21.505
It was me.

00:52:21.646 --> 00:52:28.228
And I have also learned exactly what it

00:52:28.289 --> 00:52:31.931
was that I said to Dowd that got

00:52:31.971 --> 00:52:32.731
his attention,

00:52:33.552 --> 00:52:36.454
that resolved this mess that he had made

00:52:37.653 --> 00:52:38.414
for himself,

00:52:39.675 --> 00:52:41.476
that he was announcing here in the

00:52:41.516 --> 00:52:42.456
fifty-first Psalm.

00:52:43.659 --> 00:52:45.822
That's going to lead to the majesty of

00:52:45.842 --> 00:52:47.043
the hundred and sixteenth.

00:52:52.025 --> 00:52:53.126
You see, I'm the co-author.

00:52:55.889 --> 00:52:58.351
Of the song I have loved beyond all

00:52:58.431 --> 00:53:00.773
others.

00:53:00.793 --> 00:53:04.675
The eighty ninth Mizmowr.

00:53:04.695 --> 00:53:06.016
I've learned a lot in the last two

00:53:06.036 --> 00:53:08.119
days and I look forward to sharing it

00:53:08.139 --> 00:53:08.518
with you.

00:53:09.699 --> 00:53:10.599
As we progress.

00:53:12.121 --> 00:53:12.621
Until then.

00:53:14.048 --> 00:53:15.621
May Yahowah bless and keep you all.

00:53:16.449 --> 00:53:16.811
Good night.